Titolo: All or Nothing (video game)

Anno: 1984

Descrizione: All or Nothing is an action-adventure game written by Paul Reynolds for the ZX Spectrum and released in 1984 by Abbex. The mission in All or Nothing is to retrieve secret files from an enemy camp and escape, all within a time limit. The game has an isometric display that utilises four cameras. If the character is obscured by an object, the camera will change automatically to keep the character in view.

Genere: Action-adventure 

Valutazione: N/A
